Two insurance companies are threatening to take legal action against Ford. JOHANNESBURG - Two insurance companies are threatening to take legal action against Ford.The Sunday Times is reporting that Auto &amp; General and Dial Direct have settled three claims from Ford EcoSport SUV owners whose cars burst into flames.Both companies say Ford has been notified.The EcoSport is a smaller, less expensive version of the now infamous Kuga.More than 4,500 Kugas were recalled earlier this year after 50 cases of the care bursting into flames were reported.WATCH: Ford Kuga catches fire off Voortrekker offramp